The main algae in the water is a brown clump ranging in size from a pea to a golf ball.  When struck- the algae ball will break up into dust.
Surface is covered with clumps of black goo.
Heavy rain last night.  Runoff effects already seen in color and clarity.
An algae bloom in progress.  Only slight.
Heavy rain - lots of runoff muddied the entire lake.
Partly Cloudy Very little snow past winter.   Melt was early and fairly gradual...water had a chance to settle in soil.

No additional rain... sediment had chance to settle out

Water is starting to fill with algae.
Excessive amount of HWM and coontail

3.25 inches rain in the past 48 hours.   Heavy filamentous algae.
Water temp 71 surface....lots filamentous algae.....not as much HWM as last year
Received 3.6 inches rain within 36 hours on June 16th + 17th
Received only 0.75 inches rain all of July...Secchi much improved
3.2 inches rain all of August and spread out.   Lake level did not raise.
Bloom just starting.   Looks like green ink released in spurts
Filamentous dying/HWM less populous- very pale pink stems. Bloom just starting.

Substantially less HWM compared to previous years....
